<TITLE> DU approves Tk 164 crore budget </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 25 (bdnews24.com)  The Dhaka University senate Wednesday approved a Tk 164 crore budget for fiscal 2008-09. DU treasurer Syed Abul Kalam Azad presented the budget with Tk 12 crore in deficit for the university. A total of Tk 121.07 crore or 73.82 percent of the budget for the next fiscal year will go into salaries and pensions. Tk 22.33 crore has been allocated for education support and Tk 16.93 crore for miscellaneous activities. The University Grants Commission will pay Tk 135.90 crore and DU will earn Tk 16.10 crore from its own sources. The treasurer proposed to increase examination fees to strike a balance between income and spending for examinations. He said examination-related expenditure increased by Tk 2 crore. Vice chancellor Professor SMA Faiz presided over the senate meeting. The two-day meeting ends Thursday. bdnew
